<HEAD>`Hill Street Blues' Actor Rescued After Spill From Boat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MALIBU, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Haid </PERSON>, who portrayed Officer <PERSON> Andy </PERSON> <PERSON> Renko </PERSON> on television's old `` Hill Street Blues'' and stars in the movie `` The Rescue,'' was plucked from the ocean after he took a spill off his sail boat. <PERSON> Haid </PERSON>, 40, said he was never in danger after falling from the catamaran about a mile off <LOCATION> Broad </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION> on Saturday afternoon. He said a couple pulled him from the water 45 minutes later. <PERSON> Haid </PERSON> said he fell into the water while trying to attach himself to a harness that allows him to lean out over the water as the wind-tipped boat rides on one pontoon. `` I was hooking on, my hook slipped and I went off the back,'' <PERSON> Haid </PERSON> said after the accident. His brother, who also was on the boat, lost sight of him, and went back to shore for help. The actor, who was wearing a wet suit and a life preserver, said he `` would have just floated ashore'' if the unidentified couple had n't come along.
