<FIRST>u a AM-EasterTrial     08-08 0327</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Easter Trial,0338</SECOND>
<HEAD>Easter, Sons Convicted of Murder</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A woman and her three sons were convicted Monday of murder in the deaths of three police officers whose bullet-riddled bodies lay in a motel room from which the family held police at bay for 10 hours. A <ORGANIZATION> Wayne </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> jury deliberated for 17 hours over four days in convicting <LOCATION> Alberta </LOCATION> Easter, 70, and her sons, <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Lemons </PERSON>, 44, <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Lemons </PERSON>, 48, and <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Lemons </PERSON>, 46, of three counts of first-degree murder each. Murder convictions carry mandatory life prison terms. They were charged in the deaths of Inkster Officers <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Dubiel </PERSON>, 36, and <PERSON> Clay </PERSON> <PERSON> Hoover </PERSON>, 24, and Sgt. <PERSON> Ira </PERSON> <PERSON> Parker </PERSON>, 41. The jury, which heard 13 weeks of testimony, also found the sons also were found guilty of felony firearms and felonious assault charges. There were many trial delays because <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Lemons </PERSON> must have dialysis treatments. The police officers had been trying to serve a bad check warrant on Easter and one of the Lemons when they were shot. Easter and her sons then negotiated with police for the release of the officers, who medical witnesses testified were dead during the siege at the Bungalow Motel. Police and the Easter family exchanged gunfire during much of the night of July 9, 1987, before the family gave up early the next day. They have been jailed ever since. Easter had claimed both that the officers shot each other while exchanging gunfire with the family inside the room, and that they were shot during exchanges between the family and officers outside. But autopsy reports said the officers were killed within minutes of entering the motel room. <PERSON> Hoover </PERSON> and <PERSON> Dubiel </PERSON> were shot 29 times each, one report said. <PERSON> Dubiel </PERSON> and <PERSON> Hoover </PERSON> initially tried to serve the warrant and called for help from <PERSON> Parker </PERSON> when Easter asked for a delay in her arrest, saying she wanted to try to straighten the matter out without going to jail.
