<HEAD>Secretary of State Sixth in Cabinet Service</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Shultz Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> joined the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration in 1982 and, combined with previous tasks during his service to President <PERSON> Nixon </PERSON>, he has spent 11 years as a Cabinet officer, sixth on the all-time list. During his tenure as secretary of <ORGANIZATION> state </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> has flown over 1 million miles to more than 70 countries, and it was on a visit to <LOCATION> Bolivia </LOCATION> on Monday that he had his closest brush with danger. A bomb exploded as his motorcade was making its way from the airport to downtown La Paz, but <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> and other members of his party escaped injury. When <PERSON> Alexander </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Haig </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> resigned unexpectedly as secretary in June 1982, President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> was intent on finding a replacement who could win swift <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> confirmation. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> settled quickly on <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>, whose appointment was greeted with bipartisan praise. He assumed his duties less than a month later, becoming the first official in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> history to serve in four Cabinet-level posts _ State, <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> and the Office of Management and Budget. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>'s most significant achievement has been was a treaty with the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> to abolish all <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> and Soviet intermediate-range nuclear missiles. His biggest disappointments thus far have been the administration's inability to bring about peace and democracy in <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> and to promote <LOCATION> Arab-Israeli </LOCATION> peace negotiations. But <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> can not be faulted for lack of effort. He has made four trips to the <LOCATION> M