<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Duchess of <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, 28-year-old wife of Prince <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON>, gave birth today to a 6 lb. 12 oz. daughter, the couple's first child who is fifth in line to the British throne, Buckingham Palace said Mother and child are both doing well, the palace said. <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Duke </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> and second son of Queen <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON>, was with his wife when she was `` safely delivered of a daughter at 8:18 p.m. -LRB- 3:18 p.m EDT -RRB- today,'' the palace said. `` Her Royal Highness and the child are both well,'' the palace statement concluded. The 28-year-old prince, a <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> lieutenant, returned to <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> on Sunday from <LOCATION> Singapore </LOCATION>, where he has been on duty with the ship HMS <LOCATION> Edinburgh </LOCATION>, to be on hand for the birth. <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> drove his wife to the rear entrance of <LOCATION> Portland </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> from their rented home 21 miles west of <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> this morning. The prince left the hospital briefly but spent the rest of the day and evening with her. The duchess' mother, <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Barrantes </PERSON>, who had flown from her home in <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> for the birth, also was at the hospital. The queen, who was opening a new Lever Brothers soap-making plant at Port Sunlight on the Wirral in northwest <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>, joked earlier in the day that the baby was taking a long time to arrive. `` We hope it is soon. We are fed up with waiting,'' the queen told young mother <PERSON> Heidi </PERSON> <PERSON> Courtney </PERSON> during a tour of the plant earlier today. Mrs. <PERSON> Courtney </PERSON>'s 22-month-old blonde, curly-haired daughter <PERSON> Carla </PERS