r areas of <ORGANIZATION> NTSB </ORGANIZATION> concern at <LOCATION> O'Hare </LOCATION> were: _ Continuing excessive overtime with many controllers saying they are required to work six-day weeks. _ Shortages in the number of controllers. While the <ORGANIZATION> FAA </ORGANIZATION> has authorized additional controllers at <LOCATION> O'Hare </LOCATION>'s radar facility, the number of controllers there actually has increased by only five in the last two years, investigators said. _ The need for newer and better computer, radar and communications equipment. Some of the equipment has been in use at other facilities for years, the safety board said. It said that 26 other <ORGANIZATION> FAA </ORGANIZATION> facilities are currently scheduled to received the <ORGANIZATION> FAA </ORGANIZATION>'s most advanced terminal radar system before it is scheduled to come to <LOCATION> O'Hare </LOCATION>
