<HEAD>NBC Sees Little Effect Of Strike On Fall Scheduling</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Writers Strike</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The five-month writers strike that just ended will push back <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s mid-season replacements a month or so, but otherwise the network is in good shape for the fall, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entertainment </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Brandon </PERSON> <PERSON> Tartikoff </PERSON> said Monday. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> will have two weeks of prime-time coverage of the Summer Olympics beginning Sept. 15. That made the network less vulnerable to delays in the new season of entertainment shows caused by the strike, but had threatened to devalue the promotional platform afforded by the multimillion-dollar Olympics coverage. `` We've had a lot of time to sort of digest what was happening and prepare for the day when it -LRB- the strike -RRB- would be over,'' <PERSON> Tartikoff </PERSON> told a news conference, though he added, `` I would say nobody's in fighting form.'' Most of <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s schedule will premiere in October. Three shows that make up the Tuesday lineup, `` <PERSON> Matlock </PERSON>,'' `` In the Heat of the Night'' and `` Midnight Caller,'' will be delayed until the end of November because of <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s airing of its miniseries `` War and Remembrance'' that month, not directly because of the strike, <PERSON> Tartikoff </PERSON> said. Premiering the week of Oct. 3 will be `` ALF,'' `` The <PERSON> Hogan </PERSON> Family,'' `` Unsolved Mysteries,'' `` Highway to Heaven,'' `` The Cosby Show,'' `` A Different World,'' `` Dear <PERSON> John </PERSON>,'' `` <PERSON> Sonny </PERSON> <PERSON> Spoon </PERSON>,'' `` 227,'' `` Amen,'' `` Golden Girls,'' `` Empty Nest'' and `` The Magical World of Disney.'' The week of Oct. 24 will have `` Tattinger's,'' `` Something Is Out There,'' `` <PERSON> Hunter </PERSON>,'' `` Family Ties'' and `` Day by Day.'' The next week, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> will add `` Baby Boom,'' `` Night Court,'' `` Cheer