<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 British actor <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Napier </PERSON>, whose butler character tidied up the Bat Cave but never divulged his master's identity in the 1960s `` Batman'' television series, died Monday at the age of 85. <PERSON> Napier </PERSON> died at the <LOCATION> Berkley </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Convalescent </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Monica </LOCATION>, where he had been living since June, said nursing supervisor <PERSON> Naseem </PERSON> <PERSON> Chunara </PERSON>. He suffered a stroke last year and had been ill for several days, she said. In a career that spanned four decades, the tall, elegant Englishman appeared in more than 50 films, including `` My Fair Lady,'' `` Tender is the Night,'' and `` Journey to the Center of the Earth.'' His best-remembered role, however, was <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Pennyworth </PERSON>, <PERSON> Batman </PERSON>'s trusted servant in the television series. The `` Batman'' series, based on the comic strip, achieved enormous popularity during its short run from January 1966 to March 1968 with its campy dialogue and celebrity villains. <PERSON> Adam </PERSON> <PERSON> West </PERSON> played the Caped Crusader and <PERSON> Burt </PERSON> <PERSON> Ward </PERSON> was his sidekick <PERSON> Robin </PERSON>, the Boy Wonder. Guest villains included <PERSON> Burgess </PERSON> <PERSON> Meredith </PERSON> as the <LOCATION> Penquin </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Cesar </PERSON> <PERSON> Romero </PERSON> as the Joker, <PERSON> Vincent </PERSON> <PERSON> Price </PERSON> as <ORGANIZATION> Egghead </ORGANIZATION> and the late <PERSON> Victor </PERSON> <PERSON> Buono </PERSON> as King <PERSON> Tut </PERSON>. <PERSON> Batman </PERSON>'s cover identity was that of millionaire <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Wayne </PERSON>. <PERSON> Pennyworth </PERSON> worked in both the above-ground <PERSON> Wayne </PERSON> mansion and in the Bat Cave crime lab, where 