<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The discovery of new planets and of complex organic chemicals in comets is encouraging astronomers to intensify their search of the universe for intelligent life beyond the <LOCATION> Earth </LOCATION>. `` The circumstantial evidence is mounting every day'' that intelligent life could have developed elsewhere in the universe, <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Klein </PERSON>, manager of <ORGANIZATION> NASA </ORGANIZATION>'s radio search for life, said Monday. `` It is encouraging.'' <PERSON> Klein </PERSON> said discoveries announced last week that planet-like objects have been found orbiting distant stars, and that organic chemicals thought to be the precursors to life exist in comets support fundamental theories about life evolving from cosmic chemistry. `` That is the circumstantial evidence that life exists elsewhere,'' <PERSON> Klein </PERSON> said. `` We know now that the materials are there. It gives us a good feeling that we are on the right track.'' He commented at the 20th assembly of the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Astronomical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION>, which is meeting in <LOCATION> Baltimore </LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Months behind in an industry where everything is due last week, producers and scriptwriters scrambled Monday to regroup after a 22-week strike that idled thousands and devastated the fall television schedule. The Writers Guild of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> membership Sunday voted 2,111 to 412, or by 83.7 percent, in favor of the pact with the <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Picture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Television </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Producers </ORGANIZATION>. `` I would say nobody's in fighting form,'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entertainment </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Brandon </PERSON> <PERSON> Tartikoff </PERSON> said. The walkout crippled <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION> and left the upcoming TV season in shambles. The season's start will be delayed, perhaps until mid-October or later, despite the anticipated glut of written material. The production season for prime-time television usually begins in late June and early July.
