<HEAD>With BC-South Korea-Spotlight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here are some basic facts about <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>. POPULATION _ 41 million people. GEOGRAPHY _ A small, mountainous country about the size of <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> or <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> occupies the southern half of the <LOCATION> Korean </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Peninsula </LOCATION> jutting into the Sea of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> and the Yellow Sea. Its only border is with <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>, but it iarby <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>. The country has hot, humid summers and very cold winters. GOVERNMENT _ A republic with a strong presidential system under which s neighbor to nethe presidency initiates most programs and the prime minister and cabinet ministers have little power. The unicameral <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION> is playing a growing role. The country, dominated by political strongmen for most of its history, had never had a peaceful transfer of power until <PERSON> Roh </PERSON> <PERSON> Tae-woo </PERSON> succeeded <PERSON> Chun </PERSON> <PERSON> Doo-hwan </PERSON> as president in February. <PERSON> Chun </PERSON>, a former general, took power with military backing in 1980. HISTORY _ <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>'s history can be traced to at least the 1st century B.C. Small rival kingdoms fought for control of the <LOCATION> Korean </LOCATION> peninsula over the centuries, with <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> often dominating the area. <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> seized the country in 1910 and proclaimed it a province. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> and Soviet forces ended the harsh Japane $ 895,000 Per Share $ 0.07 $ 0.15
