<SECOND>PM-Twilight Zone Revisited,0718</SECOND>
<HEAD>Lingering Turmoil Surrounds Movie Tragedy</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LINDA DEUTSCH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Six years after <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>'s deadliest movie accident and a year after a celebrated trial, the `` Twilight Zone'' remains a nagging dilemma for the movie industry. Scrutiny of the helicopter crash that killed veteran actor <PERSON> Vic </PERSON> <PERSON> Morrow </PERSON> and two child actors has resumed with the publication of a book about the trial of the director, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Landis </PERSON>, and four co-defendants. Another book on the subject is due next month. Participants still debate details of the crash that occurred July 23, 1982, during filming of a Vietnam War scene for `` Twilight Zone: The Movie.'' The helicopter crashed during special effects explosions, also killing 6-year-old <PERSON> Renee </PERSON> <PERSON> Chen </PERSON> and <PERSON> Myca </PERSON> <PERSON> Dinh </PERSON> <PERSON> Le </PERSON>, 7. Attorney <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Neal </PERSON>, who successfully defended <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> against manslaughter charges in <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, says the case should be `` over and done with.'' `` The reason it wo n't go away,'' says attorney <PERSON> Harland </PERSON> <PERSON> Braun </PERSON>, `` is because the system never assessed moral responsibility and no one accepted moral responsibility. `` <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> has never said, ` I did the wrong thing,''' said <PERSON> Braun </PERSON>, who represented associate producer <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Folsey </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> at the trial. Despite a jury's acquittal of <PERSON> Landis </PERSON>, <PERSON> Folsey </PERSON> and the co-defendants of involuntary manslaughter, <PERSON> Braun </PERSON> and two other defense attorneys _ <PERSON> Arnold </PERSON> <PERSON> Klein </PERSON>, representing special effects coordinator <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Stewart </PERSON>, and <PERSON> Eugene </PERSON> <PERSON> Trope </PERSON>, representing pilot <PERSON> Dorcey </PERSON> <PERSON> Wingo </PERSON> _ believe an acknowledgment of responsibility was called for. `` I do n't think much of <PERSON> Landis </PERSON>,'' said <PERSON> Klein </PERSON>. `` He had a cowardly defense where he blamed everyone else. He never came out and said he was deeply sorry for that which he was responsible for.'' Author <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Labrecque </PERSON>, whose book `` Special Effects'' is due next month, said <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> fuels controversy with his own actions. For example: _ In early summer, <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> gave a dinner party at a trendy <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION> restaurant on the first anniversary of his acquittal Attorney <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON> <PERSON> Levine </PERSON>, a guest, said it was a `` nice'' gesture by <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> to thank those who stood by him. _ In June, <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> invited the trial jurors to a private screening of `` Coming to <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>,'' the <PERSON> Eddie </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> film he directed The jurors accepted, and <PERSON> Landis </PERSON>' action drew more criticism. In their newly published book, `` Outrageous Conduct: Art, Ego and the Twilight Zone Case,'' authors <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> Farber </PERSON> and <PERSON> Marc </PERSON> <PERSON> Green </PERSON> sharply criticize <PERSON> Landis </PERSON>, the prosecutor who lost the case and the movie industry that failed to penalize <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> for the deaths. `` There are elements of <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION> that are morally bankrupt,'' said <PERSON> Green </PERSON>. `` They believe only in the bottom line, and as long as <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Landis </PERSON>' name is above the title of a movie that is the highest grossing non-sequel in history -LRB- `` Coming to <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'' -RRB-, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> will be welcome in those quarters.'' `` No one asks questions,'' said <PERSON> Farber </PERSON>. <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> refused to be comment on the matter. His <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> lawyer, <PERSON> Joel </PERSON> <PERSON> Behr </PERSON>, said the director was in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> and would not comment even if he were here. <PERSON> Neal </PERSON> said <PERSON> Landis </PERSON> acknowledged his role in the accident when he testified at the trial and should be allowed to `` get on with his life.'' `` They did wrong, and certainly it can be argued they were guilty of violating child labor laws. But it should be over and it should be done with,'' he said. <PERSON> Neal </PERSON>, his associate, <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Sanders </PERSON>, and <PERSON> Levine </PERSON>, who represented production manager <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Allingham </PERSON> in the manslaughter trial, have cameo roles in `` Coming To <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>.'' Another key player in the `` Twilight Zone'' drama continues to make news. <PERSON> Lea </PERSON> <PERSON> Purwin </PERSON> <PERSON> D'Agostino </PERSON>, the deputy district attorney who spent 10 months prosecuting the case, ran for District Attorney against her boss, <PERSON> Ira </PERSON> <PERSON> Reiner </PERSON>, in June. She lost and has been transferred to a lesser job. She calls the reassignment retaliation. `` No one is letting me forget it,'' she said. `` Probably, because it's <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>. But there's also the enormity of the horror, the absolutely needless loss of life for a lousy movie.'' But Chief Deputy District Attorney <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON> <PERSON> Garcetti </PERSON> denied the reassigment was vindictive. He said plans to move Mrs. <PERSON> D'Agostino </PERSON> to the other job were made several months ago and were not related to the `` Twilight Zone'' verdict.
