lphia </LOCATION> that reach about 19.4 percent of the country's viewers Federal regulations limit a network to owning no more than 12 stations reaching a maximum 25 percent of the country. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> already has an affiliate in <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>, but the station, <ORGANIZATION> WTVJ </ORGANIZATION>, was acquired by <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> last year for about $ 270 million. That station has continued to carry CBS programs, however, under an affiliation agreement that ends in January. <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> is the nation's 16th largest television market. `` The exciting and fast-growing <LOCATION> Maimi </LOCATION> market offers a terrific expansion opportunity for us,'' said <PERSON> Eric </PERSON> <PERSON> Ober </PERSON>, president of the CBS-owned television station division. <PERSON> Tisch </PERSON> was quoted in a statement as saying the purchase `` reflects the commitment of the board and senior management to make sound investments in good broadcast properties in attractive local markets.'' `` We are continuing to evaluate other potential properties with an eye toward further acquisitions,'' he said. Ths acquisition would be the second major purchase by <PERSON> Tisch </PERSON> in the past four months. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> bought the broadcast rights for 1992 winter Olympics for $ 243 million in May.
